Alibaba Group reports slowest-ever quarterly revenue growth1. Chinese e-commerce giant Alibaba Group Holding's net income plunged 74% in the October to December period while revenue grew by just 10% to 242.6 billion yuan ($38.35 billion)  the slowest pace in a single quarter.2. Alibaba's revenue was lower than the 246.37 billion yuan average estimate among analysts surveyed by Refinitiv.3. Daniel Zhang  Alibaba's chairman and chief executive officer  blamed the slower growth on the resurgence of COVID-19  China's macroeconomy slowdown and increasing competition from rivals such as Pinduoduo JD.com  and live sales platforms such as Douyin and Kuaishou.More here
